                                                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="12704830" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 30 Apr 2009 22:51:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do for 0.20.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711721" author="stack" created="Thu, 21 May 2009 17:43:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re on the 0.1 trunk of thrift.  That good enough to close this issue? (Let &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1369&quot; title=&quot;drop in 0.1 jar and regenerate when Thrift 0.1 is available&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1369&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1369&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; cover adding 0.1 thrift when released and leave it as it is, not be in the way of 0.20.0?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711759" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 21 May 2009 19:09:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Move out of 0.20.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12790167" author="lars_francke" created="Mon, 14 Dec 2009 14:07:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thrift 0.2.0 has just been released. I&apos;d like to upgrade to this version while doing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1744&quot; title=&quot;Thrift server to match the new java api.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1744&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1744&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12790279" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Dec 2009 18:39:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Lars&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801307" author="lars_francke" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 02:01:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As a first step this could be done now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately Thrift 0.2 introduces two new .jar dependencies. SLF4J:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;slf4j-api-1.5.8.jar&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;slf4j-simple-1.5.8.jar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;As two different Thrift versions can cause problems and the current Thrift API will stay at least for 0.21 we need those dependencies and the new Thrift 0.2 jar in the core dependencies. All three can be removed once thrift moves out of the core and only to contrib.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SLF4J is in the Maven repositories so Ivy should be able to pull those. I&apos;ve added a patch that adds SLF4J though someone familiar with Ivy should probably check that it&apos;s correct. Should I attach the new libthrift-0.2.0.jar to this ticket as well? It can be generated easily from the thrift release &lt;a href=&quot;http://incubator.apache.org/thrift/download/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://incubator.apache.org/thrift/download/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801317" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 05:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The latest trunk seems to contains commons-lang as well ( in addition to slf4j )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;dependency org=&quot;commons-lang&quot; name=&quot;commons-lang&quot; rev=&quot;2.4&quot; conf=&quot;* -&amp;gt; *,!sources,!javadoc&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should that be added explicitly as well ? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also the &apos;changing=&quot;true&quot;&apos; does not need to be present for these dependencies, since these are static with well-defined release process. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is mainly reserved for hadoop-core/hdfs/mapred at this point using maven .snapshot symlink for their repositories. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801318" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 06:03:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;while we are at this - I have put a patch at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-363&quot; title=&quot;Maven Deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to help to publish to mvn repositories. That should help us handle tasks like this relatively easy. Interested people can vote on the patch to help that process moving along. Thanks. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801321" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 06:09:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1360&quot; title=&quot;move up to Thrift 0.2.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1360&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1360&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with changes attached again. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801322" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 06:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lars - can you help check the patch once again. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801428" author="lars_francke" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 16:02:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot for the help! I just copied the other &amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt; declarations - thanks for fixing this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are also correct about commons-lang. It is used solely for the generation/implementation of proper hashcode functions for the generated types so it is optional but I think it is a good idea to have it. Thanks for catching this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Everything seems to work just fine with your latest patch!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801489" author="stack" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 20:03:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lars and Kay Kay, so you want me to apply this last patch to TRUNK?  It moves us to thrift 0.2 (Should we rename this issue?).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801495" author="lars_francke" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 20:21:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve renamed the issue as per your suggestion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As Kay Kay has done a wonderful job on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-363&quot; title=&quot;Maven Deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I think it&apos;s best that we wait until that is resolved or at least until Kay Kays latest comment is answered. If they decide to publish 0.2.0 too we can simplify this and need not check in the new .jar file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801499" author="stack" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 20:45:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lars Francke &amp;#8211; sounds like a good tactic to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801509" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 21:14:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;@Lars and Kay Kay, so you want me to apply this last patch to TRUNK? It moves us to thrift 0.2 (Should we rename this issue?).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am ok with applying this patch to trunk and keep this ball rolling. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-363&quot; title=&quot;Maven Deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - a good chunk of it is done - but it is going to be sometime before the thrift dev decides on a release process / build etc. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After it is done - we can always create another patch to remove thrift from ivy.xml altogether and integrate.  So for now - green with this patch and go ahead please.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801510" author="stack" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 21:19:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm... OK.  Do I need to update the thrift jar?  Or just keep what we currently have checked in to the lib dir?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801514" author="kaykay.unique" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 21:24:28 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hmm... OK. Do I need to update the thrift jar? Or just keep what we currently have checked in to the lib dir?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am not very familiar with hbase-thrift integration details .  Lars - you have a suggestion for the process ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801519" author="lars_francke" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 21:46:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached the new libthrift-0.2.0.jar which should replace the old libthrift-r771587.jar in the lib/ directory. This will only work though if the additional dependencies from Kay Kays latest patch are added too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should hopefully be okay because Thrift is released under the Apache License as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801989" author="stack" created="Mon, 18 Jan 2010 23:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I need to regenerate thrift classes before I can apply this or do you want to add a patch that removes the old generated code and adds the new?   Also, Lars, do you want to update this doc. of the thrift package especially since you have fancy new options: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/hbase/docs/r0.20.2/api/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/thrift/package-summary.html#package_description?&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/hbase/docs/r0.20.2/api/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/thrift/package-summary.html#package_description?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12802053" author="lars_francke" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2010 02:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can attach a patch with the regenerated classes - do generated classes need the Apache license header too?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll update the doc too but I&apos;ll do that in another patch. Let&apos;s keep this solely for the Thrift update. I&apos;ll have a look if there is an appropriate ticket already or open a new one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12802076" author="stack" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2010 03:55:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it is no bother to you, please attach a patch w/ generated classes.  Else I&apos;ll have a go at it.  The current generated classes have an apache license.  Is this just mod of a template?   Good on you Lars.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12802242" author="lars_francke" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2010 13:26:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a patch against the current trunk to bring the generated Thrift classes up to version 0.2.0 of Thrift. I&apos;ve added the Apache license header to every file.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve also updated the relevant parts of the package documentation for now. The only thing that has changed is that the structs now implement a proper hashcode function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other improvements to the old Thrift API will come in a separate issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803021" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2010 22:12:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All tests pass.  Committed to TRUNK.  Great work lads (Lars Francke and Kay Kay).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017765" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 13:01:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
